The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network (DCNN) architecture for lodging classification using images from canola and wheat breeding trials. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses transfer learning and handcrafted texture features, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also involves automatic detection and prediction, which are key aspects of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
